        <p>
            <b> The 8 Functional System Scales</b>
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><b>Pyramidal – </b><span>weakness or difficulty moving limbs</span></li>
            <li><b>Cerebellar – </b><span>ataxia, loss of coordination or tremor</span></li>
            <li><b>Brainstem – </b><span>problems related to impairment of cranial nerves</span></li>
            <li><b>Sensory – </b><span>loss of sensory modalities</span></li>
            <li><b>Bowel and Bladder </b><span>function</span></li>
            <li><b>Visual</b> <span>function</span></li>
            <li><b>Cerebral </b><span>(or mental) functions</span></li>
            <li><b>Others</b></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            Each functional system is scored on a scale of 0 (no impairment or disability) to 5 or 6 
            (more severe impairment or disability).
        </p>
