        <p>
            Although the disabilities are placed in an approximate order of how they are likely 
            to occur as the disease progresses, progression through these stages is unlikely to be linear.
        </p>
        <div class="keypoint">
            The EDSS is in widespread use and its common language is familiar to neurologists. It is 
            considered easy to use being based on neurological examination, uses a relatively 
            straightforward scoring system and has considerable evidence to support its reliability.
        </div>

        <p>
            <a href="#" class="deepdive" rel="deepdivepopup1">Full details of the EDSS scale can be found here.</a>
        </p>
        <div id="deepdivepopup1" class="deepdivepopup">
            <div class="centeredimage">
                <div class="imagegroup">
                    <img src="images/16_M3_T8.jpg" alt="" />
